[SN]TITLE[SN]
Adam Peaty & Siobhan-Marie O'Connor win European silvers

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Adam Peaty and Siobhan Marie O'Connor added to Great Britain's medal tally with silvers at the European Short Course Championship in Israel.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Peaty won his second silver of the week, finishing 0.18 seconds behind Germany's Marco Koch in the 100m breaststroke.
He was runner-up in the 50m breaststroke earlier in the event.
O'Connor finished second to Hungary's Katinka Hosszu in the women's 200m individual medley.
Hosszu set a new championship record of two minutes 2.53 seconds, with O'Connor clocking 2:05.13 for her second silver of the meeting, which finishes on Sunday.
